external_knowledge:
- "Bustling marketplaces" refers to cities and categories where properties are sold;
- "Golden apples of real estate transactions" metaphorically refers to the properties themselves, highlighting their value;
- The average sale price represents the typical selling price of these properties in a given city and category;
- The sales volume indicates the number of transactions.

sql:
SELECT p.property_id, p.price, c.city_name
FROM properties p
JOIN cities c ON p.cityCode = c.city_code;

SELECT property_id, squareMeters, numberOfRooms, cityCode, cityPartRange
FROM properties
WHERE price > 1000000 AND property_status = 'for sale';
